# CSS Styling Standards

## Color Scheme
- **Primary Background**: `#0a1929` (dark blue)
- **Secondary Background**: `#1e293b` (lighter dark blue)
- **Text Color**: `#e8f4fd` (light blue-white)
- **Accent Colors**: `#3b82f6` (blue), `#10b981` (green), `#ef4444` (red)
- **Border Colors**: `#475569`, `#334155`

## Typography
- **Font Family**: `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif`
- **Line Height**: `1.6` for readability
- **Font Sizes**: Use rem units for scalability
- **Heading Hierarchy**: Clear visual distinction between h1, h2, h3

## Layout Principles
- **Mobile First**: Design for mobile, enhance for desktop
- **CSS Grid & Flexbox**: Use modern layout techniques
- **Responsive Breakpoints**: 
  - Mobile: `< 768px`
  - Tablet: `768px - 1024px`
  - Desktop: `> 1024px`

## Component Styling
```css
.component-name {
    /* Layout */
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    
    /* Spacing */
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    
    /* Visual */
    background: #1e293b;
    border: 2px solid #475569;
    border-radius: 8px;
    
    /* Typography */
    color: #e8f4fd;
    font-size: 1rem;
    
    /* Transitions */
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.component-name:hover {
    border-color: #3b82f6;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
}
```

## Accessibility Features
- **Focus States**: Clear focus indicators for keyboard navigation
- **Color Contrast**: Minimum 4.5:1 ratio for normal text
- **Touch Targets**: Minimum 44x44px for mobile interactions
- **Screen Reader**: `.sr-only` class for hidden content

## Responsive Design
- Use CSS Grid for complex layouts
- Implement flexible containers with max-widths
- Use media queries for breakpoint-specific styles
- Ensure content remains readable on all screen sizes

## Performance
- Minimize CSS specificity conflicts
- Use CSS custom properties for repeated values
- Optimize animations with `transform` and `opacity`
- Avoid expensive properties in animations
